Kenzo Takada succumbed to complications linked to coronavirus at the age of 81. TOKYO - The Japanese founder of popular fashion brand Kenzo has died. Kenzo Takada succumbed to complications linked to coronavirus at the age of 81. Takada was known for his bright graphics and eclectic use of colour. He was the first Japanese designer to gain prominence on the Paris fashion scene. He founded Kenzo in the 1970s before selling it to luxury firm LVMH in 1993 when he retired from fashion Takada died at the American Hospital in Paris.